name: configure
desc: Reconfigures a participant already attached to the audio bridge.

name: createRoom
desc: Creates a new audio bridge room and returns its descriptor.

name: editRoom
desc: Updates mutable metadata for an existing audio bridge room.

name: hangup
desc: Sends a leave request after performing the base hangup cleanup.

name: joinRoom
desc: Joins an audio bridge room and optionally overrides per-participant settings.

name: kickParticipant
desc: Removes a participant from the room when the admin secret is provided.

name: listParticipants
desc: Returns the list of participants currently joined to roomId.

name: muteParticipant
desc: Mutes or unmutes a participant when the caller holds the room secret.

name: onCreate
desc: Wires audio-bridge specific typed events after the plugin is attached.

name: rtpForward
desc: Starts forwarding room audio to an external RTP endpoint.

name: stopRtpForward
desc: Stops a previously created RTP forwarder for the audio bridge room.

name: JanusClient.new
desc: JanusClient

desc: Get janus server verbose information more like found on path /info

name: createAnswer
desc: Creates an SDP answer and sets it as the local description.

name: createOffer
desc: Creates an SDP offer and sets it as the local description.

name: dispose
desc: Disposes timers, stream controllers, transports, and media tied to this plugin.

name: exists
desc: Checks whether a Janus room identified by roomId exists.

name: getAudioInputDevices
desc: Returns all available audio input devices from the underlying platform.

name: getBitrate
desc: Calculates the bitrate of the inbound video stream identified by mid.

name: getBitrateMeasurement
desc:
Returns a strongly typed bitrate measurement that can be formatted or
transformed as desired by the caller.

name: getNetworkQuality
desc: Produces a single network quality snapshot using the underlying stats.

name: getVideoInputDevices
desc: Returns all available video input devices from the underlying platform.

name: handleRemoteJsep
desc: Applies the remote RTCSessionDescription provided by Janus to this peer connection.

name: hangup
desc: Stops polling and disposes media resources without fully disposing the handle.

name: initDataChannel
desc: Creates the default data channel when missing for TextRoom/data usage.

name: initializeMediaDevices
desc:
Initializes device media (camera, microphone, or display capture) and
wires the resulting stream into the plugin's peer connection.

name: initializeWebRTCStack
desc: Initializes or re-initializes the internal WebRTC stack for this plugin.

name: mediaStats
desc: Exposes WebRTC statistics helpers (bitrate calculations, history, etc.).

name: send
desc: Sends a Janus message with optional SDP negotiation data.

name: sendData
desc: Sends a text message over the default data channel.

name: switchCamera
desc: Switches the active camera track to the one referenced by deviceId.

name: watchNetworkQuality
desc: Continuously samples network quality and emits high-level snapshots.

name: watchNetworkQualityLevel
desc: Convenience wrapper that emits only the NetworkQuality level.

name: attach
desc:
This can be used to attach plugin handle to the session.
opaqueId : opaque id is an optional string identifier used for client side correlations in event handlers or admin API.

name: accept
desc: Accepts an incoming SIP INVITE and negotiates WebRTC when required.

name: call
desc: Initiates a SIP INVITE toward uri and negotiates a media session.

name: decline
desc: Declines an incoming SIP call with an optional custom response.

name: hangup
desc: Sends a SIP BYE to terminate the active dialog.

name: hold
desc: Places the call on hold using the provided direction.

name: onCreate
desc: Registers typed event mapping specific to the SIP plugin.

name: recording
desc: Starts or stops recording of the current SIP session.

name: register
desc: Registers the plugin as a SIP endpoint with the remote registrar.

name: transfer
desc: Transfers the active dialog to another SIP endpoint.

name: unhold
desc: Resumes media after a previous hold request.

name: unregister
desc: Unregisters the current account from the SIP server.

name: update
desc: Refreshes the SIP session, typically after header/contact changes.

name: JanusStreamStats
desc:
Utility wrapper around RTCPeerConnection.getStats() that offers
incremental bitrate and network quality helpers.

name: bitrate
desc:
Calculates the bitrate in bits-per-second for the RTP stream matched by
query. Consecutive invocations cache the previous sample to compute the
delta; the first call therefore returns null.

name: bitrateLabel
desc:
Returns a formatted string representation of bitrate. When no
measurement is available the result is null.

name: clearHistory
desc:
Clears cached byte counters so the next bitrate calculation restarts the
measurement window. Provide historyKey to reset a single stream.

name: networkQuality
desc:
Evaluates network quality according to thresholds. When previous is
provided it is used to decide whether missing samples should be treated as
stale (e.g. the publisher disappeared) or still warming up.

name: watchNetworkQuality
desc: Continuously samples networkQuality and emits snapshots over time.

name: createStream
desc: Creates a new streaming mount point on the Janus server.

name: destroyStream
desc: Destroys the specified mount point, optionally removing it from config when permanent is true.

name: editStream
desc: Updates metadata or access control for an existing mount point.

name: getStreamInfo
desc: Retrieves detailed information for the mount point with id.

name: listStreams
desc: Returns the list of all streaming mount points available on the server.

name: onCreate
desc: Registers typed event helpers for streaming-specific events.

name: pauseStream
desc: Temporarily pauses media delivery while keeping the session alive.

name: startStream
desc: Starts playback after a successful watchStream negotiation.

name: stopStream
desc: Stops the media flow and tears down the streaming session.

name: switchStream
desc: Switches the current subscription to another mount point.

name: watchStream
desc: Subscribes to the mount point identified by id.

name: JanusTextRoom
desc:
room : 1234
description : "Demo Room"
pin_required : false
num_participants : 0
history : 0

name: createRoom
desc: Creates a new text room.

name: destroyRoom
desc: Destroys an existing text room.

name: editRoom
desc: Updates metadata or access settings for an existing text room.

name: exists
desc: Verifies whether a text room with the given identifier exists.

name: joinRoom
desc: Joins the text room identified by roomId.

name: kickParticipant
desc: Removes a participant from the room when the admin secret is provided.

name: leaveRoom
desc: Leaves the specified text room after a successful joinRoom call.

name: listParticipants
desc: Returns the participant roster for the specified room.

name: listRooms
desc: Returns all text rooms configured on the Janus server.

name: sendMessage
desc: Sends a chat text message to the specified room.

name: setup
desc: Negotiates the peer connection and data channel used for the text room.

name: dispose
desc: this is called internally whenever JanusSession or JanusPlugin is disposed for cleaning up of active connections either polling or websocket connection.

name: acceptCall
desc: Accepts an incoming call, defaulting to an automatically generated answer.

name: call
desc: Initiates a call toward userName, creating an offer when one is not provided.

name: getList
desc: Requests the list of registered peers. Results arrive via plugin events.

name: hangup
desc: Terminates the current call and notifies the remote peer.

name: onCreate
desc: Maps raw event payloads to strongly typed video-call events.

name: register
desc: Registers the local user so they can receive and place calls.

name: set
desc: Updates media or recording preferences for the current call.

name: JanusVideoRoomPlugin
desc: Wrapper around the Janus VideoRoom plugin with typed helpers.

name: configure
desc: Reconfigures an ongoing publisher session (bitrate, recording, layers, etc.).

name: createRoom
desc: Creates a new room with the provided identifier and metadata.

name: destroyRoom
desc: Permanently removes an existing room, optionally using the admin secret.

name: editRoom
desc: Updates mutable room properties such as description, pin, or publisher caps.

name: getRoomParticipants
desc: Fetches the active publishers currently joined to roomId.

name: getRooms
desc: Lists rooms exposed by the Janus instance, including static ones.

name: hangup
desc: Tears down the subscriber connection and sends a leave request.

name: joinPublisher
desc: Joins roomId as a publisher, advertising displayName to other participants.

name: joinSubscriber
desc: Joins roomId as a subscriber against feedId and requested streams.

name: onCreate
desc: Converts raw plugindata payloads into typed video-room events.

name: publishMedia
desc: Publishes local media to existing subscribers, creating an offer when missing.

name: start
desc: Acknowledges the attach as a subscriber and starts receiving media.

name: subscribeToStreams
desc: Subscribes to the listed publisher streams, optionally sending a custom offer.

name: unpublish
desc: Requests Janus to tear down the current publisher PeerConnection.

name: unsubscribe
desc: Stops receiving the specified streams while remaining attached.

name: update
desc: Dynamically adds or removes simulcast streams on an existing subscription.

inform the plugin that we need to use WebSockets as a transport mechanism for communicating with Janus Server.
sendCompleterTimeout is used to set timeout duration for each send request to Janus server resolving against transaction.
